Arrays:
-------
An array is a container that holds fixed number of values of same type(data type).
Array store eleents in contigeous memory location
Its index starts from zero.

Syntax:
------
  Declaration: 
      datatype[] refernceName;
EX: int[] arr;
     string[] strArr;

  Initialization:   
      arr = new int[6]; - This allocate a block of memory that holds 6 integer values.

   Direct initialization:
       arr = {10, 20, 30, 40}   

   Index based:
     referenceName[index] = value;      
      EX: arr[0] = 20; arr[1] = 30


Note: If we initialize an array with 5 elements and if we are using only 3 items, then the remaning 2 non used items will have the default value of that particular data type.

Features:
  Fixed size, once created cannot be changed.
  It holds same data type.
  Indexed access.

Types of arrays:
  1. Single dimensional array.
     int[] arr = new int[5];
  2. Multidimensional array  
      int[][] arr = new int[5][5]
     

